Yes тАФ hereтАЩs a concrete Phase 1 monorepo IтАЩd ship first. IтАЩd keep the station shell and the privileged station agent separate: Tauri can handle the desktop UI and cloud WebSocket connection through its plugin, while a native Windows service runs independently and communicates with the shell over named pipes.[^1][^2][^3]

## Repo layout

Phase 1 should be a monorepo with four deployables: API, manager web app, station shell, and station service. The Tauri shell can own login/session UI, while the service owns timer persistence, game launch, process watching, and machine-level actions.[^2][^1]

